===Death and children===
General McAlpin died at 2:00 p.m. on 1 2 April 1917 at his home in Ossining of a [[cerebral hemorrhage]]. <ref>{{cite news 
  | last = 
  | first = 
  | coauthors = 
  | title = Gen. E.A. M<U+2019>Alpin (sic) Dies at Ossining
  | work = 
  | pages = 
  | language = 
  | publisher = New York Times
  | date = 13 April 1917
  | url = http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9D01E3DD153AE433A25750C1A9629C946696D6CF
  | accessdate = 9 June 2008}}</ref> He is buried at the family vault located at the [[Dale Cemetery]] in Ossining.

General McAlpin left five sons:

* Colonel Benjamin Brandreth McAlpin
* Reverend Edwin A. McAlpin
* J. Roderick McAlpin
* Kenneth R. McAlpin
* David Hunter McAlpin 2nd

